    "updated_at": "2023-11-15T10:45:30Z",
    "body": "> Personally, I wouldn't interpret this rule this strongly. That being said, if this is such a major issue for nix to support, I wouldn't be opposed to supporting list-values, as long as it doesn't break compatibility with existing configurations (e.g., via `Either<A, B>`).\n\nHonestly it would take more effort to implement in Nix than vice versa. In Starship we shouldn't even need to use an Either — just have a custom deserializer that collects into an IndexMap directly if its just a table, or converts the list of substitutions into an IndexMap if it's an array of tables. ",
