    "created_at": "2025-05-06T09:44:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-06T09:44:48Z",
    "body": "> Make directory.substitutions an array of tables, who do have a defined order. TOML even has a neat syntax for this:\n> ```toml\n> [[directory.substitutions]]\n> from = \"/a/b\"\n> to = \"b\"\n> \n> [[directory.substitutions]]\n> from = \"/a\"\n> to = \"a\"\n> ```\n\nI think we could get away with even simpler scheme:\n```toml\ndirectory.substitutions = [\n  { \"from\" = \"to\" },\n  { \"from2\" = \"to2\"},\n]\n```\nretaining similar semantics to what's there now.\n\nOr, less dry:\n``` toml\n[[directory.substitutions]]\n\"from\"  = \"to\"\n\n[[directory.substitutions]]\n\"from2\"  = \"to2\"\n```\n\nOr just move the config format to [Corn](https://cornlang.dev) :) KVs there are still not _guaranteed_ to be in order, but the spec say \"best effort to keep the order\" at least.",
